Title : Chatscah Indian Reserve No. 2
Text : '''Chatscah Indian Reserve No. 2''', officially '''Chatscah 2''' is an [[Indian reserve]] of the [[Nuxalk Nation]] [[band government]], located at the mouth of the [[Kimsquit River]] at the head of [[Dean Channel]].<ref>[http://apps.gov.bc.ca/pub/bcgnws/names/64999.html BC Names/GeoBC entry "Chatscah 2 (Indian reserve)"]</ref>  Like nearby [[Kimsquit]], at the mouth of the [[Dean River]] to the southeast, this Indian reserve was one of two reserves set aside of the once-populous Kimsquit subgroup of the [[Nuxalk]], whose surviving post-smallpox population gathered at [[Bella Coola, British Columbia|Bella Coola]].

